(b) The Board shall deny an application for a license under this section if the
Board determines that the business to be operated under this license will not enhance
recreational, business, and economic development in the county.
(c) The Board may issue the license for use by a hotel or motel that:
(1) is an establishment to accommodate the public by providing customary
hotel or motel services;
(2) has at least 10 rooms; and
(3) has a lobby with a registration and mail desk and seating facilities.
(d) The Board may issue the license for use by a restaurant that:
(1) has seating at tables, not including seats at bars or counters, for at least
20 individuals; and
(2) can prepare and serve full–course meals for at least 20 individuals at
one seating.
